15 WHEREAS, Lynne Riley represented the citizens of House District 50 in the Georgia House
16 of Representatives from 2011 to 2014 and dutifully served as a Governor's Floor Leader and
17 member of the committees on Ways & Means, MARTOC, Natural Resources &
18 Environment, and Retirement; and
19 WHEREAS, she is a devoted wife to Mike, loving mother, and adoring grandmother who has
20 always prioritized her family; and
21 WHEREAS, her significant organizational and leadership talents, remarkable patience and
22 diplomacy, keen sense of vision, and sensitivity to the needs of the citizens of this state have
23 earned her the respect and admiration of her colleagues; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
25 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately honored.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
27 recognize and commend Lynne Riley for her efficient, effective, and dedicated public service
28 to the State of Georgia as well as extend best wishes for continued success and happiness in
29 her retirement.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
31 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Lynne Riley.
